properties.areaDesc: West Slopes North Central Cascades and Passes
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 7 at 4:16PM PST until January 8 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow expected above 3000 feet. Total snow accumulations
of up to 12 inches.

* WHERE...Cascade mountains and valleys of Snohomish and King
Counties, including Darrington, Index, Skykomish, Stevens
Pass, and Snoqualmie Pass.

* WHEN...From 4 PM this afternoon to 4 AM PST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Rain or rain/snow mix will be possible this
evening ahead of an approaching cold front. Later this evening,
rain will transition back to snow as colder air moves in. The
Northwest Avalanche Center expects high avalanche danger to
continue through Wednesday. Check nwac.us for the latest
avalanche conditions.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 AM PST WEDNESDAY ABOVE 3000 FEET
